successful treatment of necrotizing soft tissue infections nsti depends on early diagnosis and therapeutical aggressiveness based on surgical debridement broad spectrum antibiotics and intensivir support case of perforated diverticulitis hinchey 4 secondary nsti is presented in order to illustrate the particular considerations in the management of abdominal wall located nsti supported on the evidence available in scientific literature several key points are identified such as prompt and aggressive surgical debridement culture guided antibiotherapy and its suspension based on microbiological negativization and the utilization of combined techniques of autoplastic repair and replacement also supported on negative pressure therapy in the abdominal wall restoration which have shown good outcome exito tratamiento infeccion necrotizant tejido blando intb depender precocidad diagnostico agresividad terapeutico basado desbridamiento quirurgico antibioticoterapia amplio espectro soporte intensivo presentar caso intb secundario diverticuliti agudo perforado hinchey 4 fin ilustrar consideracion particular manejo intb localizacion pared abdominal apoyado evidencia disponible literatura cientifico identificar punto clave precocidad agresividad desbridamiento quirurgico antibioticoterapia dirigido cultivo suspension guiado negativizacion microbiologico empleo tecnica combinada autoplastia protesis apoyado terapia presion negativo restauracion pared abdominal haber obtener buen resultado